    "revise": "You are the FIGURE REVISER (Opus) for \"The LLM Stack\". Chapter: content/10-multimodal-and-arch/01-vision-transformers.md\nThe chapter's core intuitions: Patches-as-tokens: a 224x224 image is cut into a grid of 16x16 patches, each flattened and linearly projected into a D-dim vector, so an image becomes an ordinary token sequence a vanilla Transformer can eat.; The whole ViT forward pass is just BERT: [CLS | patch tokens] + learned positional embeddings, L Pre-LN Transformer blocks, then read the CLS row as the global image representation.; The CLIP contrastive objective builds an NxN image-text similarity matrix and trains the diagonal (matching pairs) to win a softmax over its whole row AND its whole column - the off-diagonal cells are the negatives, which is why huge batches matter.; SigLIP swaps CLIP's row/column softmax for an independent sigmoid on every cell of the NxN grid, so there is no cross-cell normalization to gather across GPUs - each pair is its own yes/no binary decision, which shards trivially and works at small batch sizes.\n\nReview each of these figures (the ones this chapter just drew/edited):\n  vit-patchify, vit-arch-full-pipeline\n\nFor EACH: render and SEE it \u2014 `python3 scripts/preview_fig.py <NAME> --theme both` from /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook,\nthen view /tmp/figpreview/<NAME>.light.png and .dark.png. Judge strictly:\n  - Does it actually BUILD INTUITION for its concept (not just decorate)? Is it correct vs the chapter?\n  - Theme-safe (no hardcoded primary color; readable in BOTH light and dark)?\n  - Nothing clipped by the viewBox; no illegible overlaps; no tofu glyphs (ASCII only in the SVG)?\n  - Marker present in the chapter exactly once; figcaption has a bold lead + takeaway?\nIf a figure has ANY problem, FIX it: Edit /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook/figures/<NAME>.html (and re-render to confirm), or\nfix a missing/duplicate marker in the chapter. Re-verify after fixing.\n\nSet verdict per figure: good / fixed / still-broken / missing. `passed` = every figure good-or-fixed\nAND present. Return the structured object."
